05/08/2003
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro/ TIRANA, Albania -- A new border crossing was opened between Serbia-Montenegro and Albania Monday (4 August). 
The ceremony for opening the Grncar-Vrmosa checkpoint, which is the third border crossing between the two countries, was attended by the foreign ministers of both countries, as well as by other high-ranking officials. 
Officials stressed the importance of the crossing, saying it would boost relations. 
Montenegro is placing particular emphasis on the economic importance of the checkpoint. 
(ATA, Albanian News, Montenegrin Radio, BBC, Beta - 05/08/03)
